cmix was started by Paul Lansky in 1985.
RTcmix was derived from cmix by Brad Garton and David Topper in 1995.


The RTcmix Development Team (in alphabetical order)
---------------------------------------------------

Brad Garton       <garton-at-columbia.edu>
John Gibson       <johgibso-at-indiana.edu>
Doug Scott        <dscott-at-netscape.net>
David Topper      <topper-at-virginia.edu>

with

Ivica Bukvic      <ico-at-fuse.net>
R. Luke DuBois    <luke-at-columbia.edu>
Mara Helmuth      <mara.helmuth-at-uc.edu>
John Rhoads       <rhoads-at-virginia.edu>


Thanks to Bill Schottstaedt for his sndlib sound library.
(http://ccrma-www.stanford.edu/CCRMA/Software/sndlib)

Thanks to Julius O. Smith for his resample program.
(http://www-ccrma.stanford.edu/~jos/resample/index.html)

Thanks to Laurent de Soras <http://ldesoras.free.fr> for his
FFTReal class, which is our default FFT for the Offt object.

Thanks to Roger Dannenberg and others for PortMIDI, which we
use in the MIDI control plugin.

Thanks to Perry Cook and Gary Scavone for the STK library
that is used by the instruments in the insts/stk directory,
and by a few instruments in the insts/jg directory.  Thanks
also to George Essl for the BandedWG object used by the
MBANDEDWG instrument.

Thanks to Juha Nieminen <warp at iki dot fi> and Joel Yliluoma for
their FunctionParser library.  (More at: http://iki.fi/warp/FunctionParser)

Thanks to Christopher Penrose for help with Mac OS X audio I/O.

Thanks to Carl McTague and Judd Storrs for FreeBSD support.

Some instruments (pvoc, convolve) contain code from the UCSD Carl package,
whose authors were F. R. Moore, Gareth Loy, Mark Dolson and others.


